            2
          ],
          "verse_count": 1,
          "testament": "NT",
          "raw": "Acts 27:2",
          "source": "EAS"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "SMI",
      "text": "named form Adramys, brother of Croesus king of Lydia, a seaport in the province of Asia [Asia], situated on a bay of the Aegean Sea, about 70 miles north of Smyrna, in the district anciently called Aeolis, and also Mysia. See (Acts 16:7) [Mitylene] (Acts 27:2) The modern Adramyti is a poor village.",
